The paper proposes a framework for visually exploring multivariate data, which involves the use of coordinated views and similarity metrics to group biclusters. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, as it focuses on the interactive exploration of data. Additionally, the use of similarity metrics and clustering techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also deals with machine learning techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with scientific data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
